sec.p:
All APT image processing was performed on United Imaging post-processing workstation. ① B0 Map Generation: A dual gradient-echo sequence was used to generate a voxelwise B0 map. ② Motion correction: All CEST offset images and the B0 map were rigidly aligned to each other within the same APT acquisition space. ③ B0 inhomogeneity correction: The aligned B0 map was used to shift each voxel’s Z-spectrum to 0 ppm, eliminating local magnetic field offsets. ④ Registration to 3D-T1WI: The corrected CEST data were then co-registered to the 3D T1-weighted images, which were automatically segmented into 106 regions based on Desikan-Killiany atlas that comprehensively covers cortical and subcortical areas implicated in AD pathogenesis. ⑤ APT Parameter Calculation: the APT parameter—magnetization transfer ratio asymmetry (MTRasym)—was calculated for each of the 106 ROIs.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
